    <bioghist>ichard L. Zurel is an archaeologist who has conducted research on Native Americans in Michigan.</bioghist>
    <arrangement>Arranged in two series: 1.Professional papers 2. Personal photographs.</arrangement>
    <scopecontent>The Richard L. Zurel papers contain materials related to his work in the field of archaeology documenting Native American groups in Michigan: research papers, reports and notes, original photographs, slides and maps of archaeological sites, Native American reservations and artifacts. Professional papers also include materials related to the Michigan Archaeological Society and the Aboriginal Research Club of Detroit. Personal photographs include family portraits, photos of family property, as well as photos and postcards of locations in Michigan.</scopecontent>
